<section xml:id="useful-cmds-keybd-shortcuts">
	<title>Useful Commands &amp; Shortcuts</title>

	<subsection xml:id="cleanup-cmds">
		<title>Cleanup Commands</title>
		<p>
			As you use MATLAB, both the command window and workspace can quickly fill up with old information. MATLAB provides commands that let you “reset” different parts of the environment without restarting the program.
		</p>

		<table>
			<title>MATLAB Clean-up Commands</title>
			<tabular>
				<row>
					<cell><pf>clc</pf></cell>
					<cell>Clears all text from the command window.</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><pf>clear all</pf></cell>
					<cell>Removes all variables from the workspace.</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><pf>close all</pf></cell>
					<cell>Closes all open figure windows.</cell>
				</row>
			</tabular>
		</table>
	</subsection>

	<subsection xml:id="keybd-shortcuts">
		<title>Shortcuts</title>

		<table>
			<title>MATLAB Keyboard Shortcuts</title>
			<tabular top="minor" bottom="minor" left="minor" right="minor" halign="center">
				<row>
					<cell>Windows</cell><cell>Macintosh</cell><cell>Description</cell>
				</row>
				<row>
					<cell><kbd>ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>c</kbd></cell>
					<cell><kbd>Command</kbd> + <kbd>.</kbd></cell>
					<cell>terminates a running MATLAB process</cell>
				</row>
			</tabular>
		</table>
	</subsection>

</section>